> A honey-based sauce may sound like something that goes with dessert, but mild-tasting
> pork loves a sweet sauce too, especially one that has a few savory elements added
> to the mix. We recommend spooning the sauce on the roasted potatoes and side of
> green beans, too!

== Roasted Potatoes & Brussels Sprouts ==

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and
dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Toss on one side of a #baking sheet{}
with a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle}, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}.

Roast on middle rack until lightly browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes} total. (You'll
add more to the sheet after 10 minutes.)

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
chicken and cook, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{6-8%minutes} (it'll
finish cooking in Step 4).

While chicken cooks, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Peel and mince
@garlic{1%clove}.

Once potatoes have roasted 10 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven; carefully toss,
keeping on one side.

Toss green beans on empty side with a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} and a pinch of
@salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Return to middle rack until veggies are tender, ~{10-12%minutes} more.

== Chicken ==

Once chicken is browned all over, transfer to a second baking sheet.

Roast on top rack until chicken is cooked through, ~{8-12%minutes}. Transfer to a
#cutting board{}.

== Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in #pan{} used for chicken over medium heat.
Add garlic and @dried thyme{1%teaspoon}; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{2}, @honey{2%teaspoon}, and @water{1/4%cup}
(1⁄2 cup for 4 servings). Simmer, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan,
until reduced by half, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

> If sauce seems too thick, stir in a splash or two of water.

== To Serve ==

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken, green beans, and potatoes between plates. Drizzle chicken with sauce
and serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.